article.headline: Youngstown St. 70, St. Francis, Pa. 65
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. (AP) -- Byron Davis scored a career-high 21 points and John Barber added 17 to lead Youngstown State to a 70-65 win over St. Francis, Pa., on Wednesday. St. Francis (0-6) led with five minutes remaining, but Barber hit a layup and, after a Red Flash miss, turned one of his two steals into a score to turn a one-point deficit into a 61-58 lead. St. Francis cut the lead to one three times in the final 2:28. But Youngstown State (3-2) pulled away by making four free throws in the final 12 seconds, including two by Davis. Cale Nelson was 9-of-19 from the field for a career-high 25 points for St. Francis. Bassirou Dieng had 13 points and 10 rebounds.
